					<head>Kabbalah</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85018546" rend="visible">
						<summary>A collection of kabbalistic works. </summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="1r" to="53v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sha῾are orah</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">שערי אורה</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/122229986">Gikatilla, Joseph ben Abraham</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/122229986">ג'יקטיליה, יוסף בן אברהם</persName>
							</author>
							<listBibl>
								<bibl>
									<ref target="Shaare_orah_1959"/>
								</bibl>
							</listBibl>
							<note>
								<p>Beginning of the treatise is written in larger semi-cursive than the rest of the text. The chapter treating on the third and fourth divine names begins on folio 9v; fifth name, folio 14r; sixth name, folio 32v; seventh name, folio 37r; eighth name, folio 39v; ninth name, folio 45v; tenth name, folio 50v.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="53v" to="55v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sod Yom Kipur</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">סוד יום כפור</title>
							<incipit xml:lang="he">מצאתי בהרת טמאה.<locus n="55r"/>
							</incipit>
							<note>
								<p>The commentary on the 42-Letter Divine Name. See further <ref target="Tarbits" type="number">4</ref> (1934), p. 60.</p>
							</note>
							<filiation>Cf. the contents of MS Milano - Biblioteca Ambrosiana &amp; 31 SUP/2 (Milan Bern. 57), see <ref target="Ambrosiana_1933" type="number">57</ref>.</filiation>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85018546">
							<locus from="55v" to="79v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Ma῾arekhet ha-elohut</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">מערכת האלהות</title>
							<listBibl>
								<bibl>
									<ref target="Maarekhet_haelohut_1557"/>
								</bibl>
							</listBibl>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/31961412">Perets, active 13th century</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/31961412">גרונדי, פרץ בן יצחק</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>The work is not followed by any commentary (contrary to the printed edition of Ferrara, 1557).</p>
								<p>See further in  <ref target="Masuot_1994" type="page">357-369</ref>.</p>
							</note>
							<filiation>Cf. the contents of Add MS 26919 (<ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">750</ref>) and Harley MS 5510/XV (<ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">754</ref>).</filiation>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="79v" to="81r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sefer Mesharet Mosheh</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">ספר משרת משה</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/41078232">Kalonymos</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/41078232">קלונימוס בן קלונימוס</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>The last two chapters are missing entirely, and of the third and fourth only small portions are given.</p>
							</note>
							<filiation>Cf. the contents of Add MS 17057.</filiation>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="81r" to="82r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sefer yetsirah</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">ספר יצירה</title>
							<note>
								<p>The recension of Sefer yetsirah in 6 chapters, accompanied with a commentary of Saadia Gaon.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="82r" to="84v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sefer ḥakhmoni</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">ספר חכמוני</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/44287685">Donnolo, Shabbetai</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/44287685">דונולו, שבתי בן אברהם</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>Contains chapters 1 to 3 and a half of chapter 4. Parts of the text are crossed out on folio 84v.</p>
								<p>See further <ref target="Mancuso_2010"/>.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="84v" to="87r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Ma᾿amarim be-ḳabalah</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">מאמרים בקבלה</title>
							<note>
								<p>Includes nine short pieces in the following order: ῾Inyan ḳeshet, Ḳabalat rabi Ya῾aḳov ha-Nazir, Sodot be-ḳabalah, Perush ῾eser sefirot, ῾Ilat ha-῾ilot, Sod ha-tefilin, Sod shem shel arba῾ otiyot, ῾Eser sefirot, Ha-shem be-ḥokhmah yasad ha-arets.</p>
								<p>See further <ref target="Kiryat_Sefer" type="number">10</ref>, p. 510 and <ref target="Scholem_1948" type="page">73-74</ref>.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="87r" to="88r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush agadot ῾al derekh ḳabalah</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרוש אגדות על דרך הקבלה</title>
							<note>
								<p>From the end of page 87r (4 last lines) till the end there is a fragment of the commentary on Sefer ha-bahir.</p>
							</note>
							<filiation>Cf. similar content in MS Milano - Biblioteca Ambrosiana P 47 SUP, folios 35r-37r, <ref target="Ambrosiana_1933" type="number">30</ref>.</filiation>
							<incipit xml:lang="he">שאל ר' נהוראי ודרש מפני מה מתחיל' התור' בב.<locus n="87r"/>
							</incipit>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="88r" to="88v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush ῾eser sefirot</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרוש עשר ספירות</title>
							<incipit xml:lang="he">ועתה אודיעך כל הדברי' שהיו מתנהג' בו בעלי המרכבה אמר' שהכתר הוא גג חופתו.<locus n="88r"/>
							</incipit>
							<note>
								<p>See <ref target="Kiryat_Sefer" type="number">10</ref>, p. 498 n. 2.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="89r" to="90r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Ḥidush sidur niḳud shem ha-meyuḥad</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">חדוש סוד נקוד שם המיוחד</title>
							<filiation>Cf. also Harley MS 5510/XIII, folio 90r; Vatican - Borgiana ebr. 4; New York - Jewish Theological Seminary MS 1878; Cambridge - University Library Add. 645/1.</filiation>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/122229986">Gikatilla, Joseph ben Abraham</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/122229986">ג'יקטיליה, יוסף בן אברהם </persName>
							</author>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="90r" to="93v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Ma᾿amarim be-ḳabalah</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">מאמרים בקבלה</title>
							<note>
								<p>Contain six short pieces in the following order: Adam rishon Raziel, Ta῾alumot ḥokhmah, Perush mi kamokhah, Perush tefilah ῾al derekh ḳabalah, ῾Inyan tsuḳe ḳedarah, Birkat ha-levanah.</p>
							</note>
							<filiation>Cf. the contents of MS Milano - Ambrosiana &amp; 31 SUP., <ref target="Ambrosiana_1933" type="number">57</ref>.</filiation>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="93v" to="94r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush ῾eser sefirot</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרוש עשר ספירות</title>
							<incipit xml:lang="he">כתר עליון רז רום מעלה מפני שהחולם משובח.<locus n="93v"/>
							</incipit>
							<note>
								<p>See further <ref target="Kiryat_Sefer" type="number">10</ref>, p. 506 n. 69.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="94r" to="94v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush ῾eser sefirot</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרוש עשר ספירות</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/97324044">Jacob ben Jacob, ha-Kohen</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/97324044">יעקב בן יעקב, הכהן</persName>
							</author>
							<incipit xml:lang="he">ישתבח מי שהוא חי וקיים לעדי עד [...] ראשון לכל דבר שהוא ראשון.<locus n="94r"/>
							</incipit>
							<note>
								<p>See further <ref target="Scholem_1989" type="page">227-230</ref>.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="94v" to="97v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Ta῾ame mitsṿot</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">טעמי מצוות</title>
							<note>
								<p>Incomplete at the end.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="98r" to="111v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sha῾ar ha-razim</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">שער הרזים</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/24783259">Abulafia, Todros ben Joseph, ha-Levi</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/24783259">אבולעפיא, טודרוס בן יוסף</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>Incomplete at the beginning.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="111v" to="112v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Notes</title>
							<note>
								<p>A part of a leaf pasted on folio 111, which is otherwise blank, starts with remarks on the Throne and ends with Sod ha-sukah. On folio 112v there are some combinations of words and letters.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="113v" to="116v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush Sefer yetsirah</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרוש ספר יצירה </title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/8687273">Abraham ben David, of Posquières (attributed to him)</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/8687273">אברהם בן דוד מפוסקיר (מיוחס לו)</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>Contains a piece of the introduction only.</p>
							</note>
							<incipit xml:lang="he">ביאור ל"ב נתיבות.<locus n="113v"/>
							</incipit>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="117r" to="118v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Teshuvot</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">תשובות</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/305131833">Isaac, Sagi-Nahor</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/305131833">יצחק בן אברהם, סגי נהור</persName>
							</author>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/77127716">Eleazar ben Judah, of Worms</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/77127716"> אלעזר בן יהודה, מגרמיזה </persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>Two short responses to the inquires on prayer, the first being of Eleazar of Worms authorship, the second, beginning on folio 118r, authored by Isaac ben ha-Rabad (i.e., Isaac Sagi-Nahor). On the latter see <ref target="Abramson_1965" type="page">150-155</ref>.</p>
							</note>
							<filiation>Cf. MS Strasbourg 3936, folios 338-339.</filiation>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 15th to 16th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper.</support>
								<extent>121 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>215</height>
										<width>145</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>165</height>
										<width>105</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>121 folios (+ 2 unfoliated paper flyleaf at the beginning and at the end). Folio 1* and 120 are vellum flyleaves originally from other manuscripts.</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 8 leaves each, marked with catchwords at the end.</p>
									<p>Leaves on guards.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Stained.</p>
									<p>Incomplete at the beginning.</p>
									<p>Large lacuna after folio 97.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="42 52" writtenLines="42 52">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Initial words in square characters.</p>
									<p>Visible hard-point ruling.</p>
									<p>Some additions and comments in the margin.</p>
									<p>A number of blank leaves before folio 113.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Ashkenazi small semi-cursive script of the 15th to 16th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Na᾿um Asher bar Ya῾aḳov ha-Leṿi</name>: inscribed in an owner's entry, folio 1r.</p>
							<p>Parts of original binding with gold-tooled initials M.B. pasted on the front and back inner cover.</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>BM in-house. Boxed.</p>
								<p>Spine: 'Joseph Gikatilla. Sha'are Orah, Etc. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Reg. 16. A. X.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
